FT  30 JUL 93 / International Company News: PanCanadian Petroleum doubles
first-half profit
PANCANADIAN Petroleum, one of Canada's top three natural gas producers and a
key affiliate of the Canadian Pacific group, doubled first-half net profit
as it gained from two years of heavy investment in oil and gas production
First-half profit was CDollars 122.5m (USDollars 96m), or 98 cents a share,
against CDollars 58.3m, or 47 cents, a year earlier, on revenues of CDollars
549m, against CDollars 418m.
Second quarter per-share earnings were 49 cents against 31 cents and
revenues for the quarter advanced to CDollars 282m from CDollars 218m.
The company said the second half would bring more gains in oil production
and the outlook for gas was good with the prospect of further price rises.
